A) FOR YOUR SAFETY
1. Intended use
This software is used to configure Weidmueller's "WM-Charge Wall Home AC" (Wallbox Home) products, intended for charging electric vehicles and hybrid vehicles with charging mode 3. The Wallbox Home is intended for use in accordance with the applicable manuals. Any use of the product that deviates from the respectively valid manual is considered improper.

2. Safety instructions for configuration
WARNING!
Danger to life due to overload of the building installation. There is a risk of fire if the Wallbox Home is set beyond the load limit of the electrical installation of the infrastructure.
► All work on the building installation and the electrical installation of the product, as well as the configuration of the product, may only be performed by a qualified electrician.
► During configuration, observe the permissible maximum power or the permissible maximum current of the existing infrastructure.
► If necessary, adjust the existing infrastructure to the maximum power or current to be set before configuration, taking into account all applicable installation regulations.

Required hardware

To communicate with the charge controller a USB to RS485 converter is required. The converter should be based on the FT232 FTDI chip. It was tested with the DSD TECH SH-U11.

Connection diagram

Connect the USB to serial converter to the mounting plate with RS485 -/A to pin R1 and RS485 +/B to pin R2 (click on the image to enlarge view).

Prerequisites

The tool was tested with Opera and Edge. If you have trouble using the tool, try using these browsers and make sure they are up to date.

Firmware update

To use features like configuring the maximum charge current, a firmware update may be required. The charge controller needs to be restarted multiple times during this process. Please follow the instructions shown on screen under the firmware tab.

Configure maximum charge current

The maximum charge current is configurable between the minimum of 6A and the maximum of either 16A for the 11kW variant, or 32A for the 22kW variant. Other values will be ignored. The configuration can not be applied when the charge controller is in state B or state C.

Configure LED timeout

If LED timeout is greater than 0, the LED ring will turn itself off after the configured amount of minutes. Any change of the state will reset the timeout. The LED ring will not turn off if the charge controller is in any error state. The timeout can be set between 0 (off) and 120 minutes. The configuration can not be applied when the charge controller is in state B or state C.

Please select a port

Please see the help tab for instructions on how to connect to the charge controller.

Trying to connect ...

If it takes longer to connect check the wrirng, ensure the right port is selected
and the controller is powered. If that doesnt help a firmware update may be required.
In this case select "use manual restart".
In this case select "use manual restart" on the firmware page.
